wikipedia_page.main: William Streets (christened 28 February 1772) was an English cricketer who played in a single first-class cricket match in 1803. Streets is known to have played for Nottingham Cricket Club between 1792 and 1800 and played his only first-class match for a combined Nottinghamshire and Leicestershire side in 1803. He was christened in 1772 at Newark-on-Trent in Nottinghamshire.
